-- Mozambique to Spend $200 Million to Link Power Grid, AIM Reports
-- B y   F r e d   K a t e r e r e
-- 2012-01-23T11:40:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-23/mozambique-to-spend-200-million-to-link-power-grid-aim-reports.html
Mozambique plans to spend $200
million to connect all the districts of the country to its
national electricity grid by 2013, Agencia de Informacao de
Mocambique reported, citing Energy Minister Salvador Namburete.  The project will be funded by government, international
donors and Electricidade de Mocambique, the state power company,
the Maputo-based  news agency  cited Namburete as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Katerere in Maputo at 
 fkaterere@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
